1) Root cause confirmation (alerts/events/logs)
- The alert shows `NodeDiskPressure` on `worker-node-03`, with the source `data-sync-job` and ephemeral storage at 87%.
- Cluster events confirm the sequence:
  - `UnusualLogVolume`: `Pod data-sync-job-pod produced 42GB of log output in the last 6 hours`
  - `DiskPressure`: `Pod data-sync-job-pod is using 85% of node ephemeral storage on worker-node-03`
  - `NodeDiskPressure`: node has insufficient ephemeral storage
- Job logs confirm the runaway log/storage behavior:
  - `Write buffer overflow - spilling to disk at /tmp/sync-buffer-4721.log`
  - `Failed to write buffer: No space left on device`
  - `FATAL Sync process aborted: storage full`

